\f1\b\fs50 GREED
\f0\b0\fs28 \
\

\f1\b OVERVIEW
\f0\b0 \

\f1\b What does Greed say? I need more? \
Why? - Scarcity mentality, I need to be self-sufficient (connect back to self-exaltation)\
What does it look like? Collections of things, prizes, and people, and money.\
Why is it bad? We lean into WHAT we have and not WHO has us.\

\f0\b0 How do we overcome it? Trust in God's provision\
Why is it so hard? The world has winds and waves. There never seems to be enough. We can confuse what we WANT with what we think we NEED.\
What does it do to our soul and relationship with The Lord? Pulls out of community with others and God.\
How do you overcome this temptation? Giving away what you are tempted to hold onto. Giving releases the grip of greed.\
How is it connected to Pride? It sees money and things to own and possess and not steward. Ownership vs Stewardship.\
Practical Next Steps: Give away what has a Grip. \

\f1\b What will it cause you do externally? Cheat, steal, hoard, lie, \

